result.execSummary:
The defendant Reese Ashley Chapin was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Take/Drive Veh. w/o Consent-Abandon Veh., a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3m).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. 2:35 PM Attorney Lawrence James Lasee in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant Reese Ashley Chapin in court, in custody.  Attorney Jon G Spansail in court for Reese Ashley Chapin. VWC Rachael Race in court. Victim present in court. Court reviews updated PA efiled on 10/11/2022, doc #20. Counsel and defendant understand and agree the document does state the plea negotiations. Defendant waives reading of Amended Information. Court reviews amended count 1 and defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to count 1. Court reviews count 2 and defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to count 2. Balance of charges DRI. PLQ received/reviewed by the Court. Court finds the defendant's pleas to be made freely and voluntarily and accepts the plea. Factual basis found. Victim rights. VWC Race reads statement for victim. Court makes stmt. State's recommendation. Atty Spansail makes stmt. Atty Spansail reads letter written by defendant. Court makes stmt. Court sentence; Ct 1 I/S 9 months county jail. Ct 2 I/S 9 months county jail consecutive to count 1. Placed on DOC probation for a period of 2 years. Conditions of probation; 4 months jail w/ huber for school and/or work (in addition to Brown County jail sentence), 68 days credit, AODA assessment and follow through w/ recommended treatment, absolute sobriety, no possession/consumption of illegal drugs and/or drug paraphernalia, no contact w/ Clayton Frehse, drug users and/or drug dealers/sellers, must reside w/ parents when released, court costs of $536 and DNA surcharges of $400 payable to the COC office at the rate of $25/month commencing 11/18/2022. Submit DNA sample.  Court would consider commuting jail time if defendant complete programming offered in the OC Jail. Default of payment debt referred to SDC. Supervision fees payable to DOC. Court will grant expungement if defendant successfully completes sentence.
Expungement Review scheduled for October 18, 2022 at 07:00 am.
